00:48:10,262 --> 00:48:11,764
I've always
wanted to be a Girl Scout.

766
00:48:11,847 --> 00:48:12,848
Of course you did.

767
00:48:14,100 --> 00:48:15,684
Anybody else starving?

768
00:48:15,768 --> 00:48:17,269
All I have is gum.

769
00:48:18,562 --> 00:48:21,482
Here. I found this
in the glove compartment.

770
00:48:22,566 --> 00:48:23,859
Wait. That bag's
already been opened.

771
00:48:23,943 --> 00:48:25,111
We don't know
how long it's been in there.

772
00:48:25,194 --> 00:48:28,072
Okay, I hope you're
good at catching squirrels.

773
00:48:28,948 --> 00:48:31,575
Okay, so what's the deal
with ceiling guy?

774
00:48:31,659 --> 00:48:33,661
I told you, I don't know.

775
00:48:33,744 --> 00:48:35,037
I've never seen him before.

776
00:48:35,121 --> 00:48:36,122
Then how did you know
he was coming?

777
00:48:36,205 --> 00:48:37,206
Oh, my God.

778
00:48:37,289 --> 00:48:40,000
I'm kind of more interested
in why he's trying to kill us.

779
00:48:40,084 --> 00:48:42,294
I don't know.

780
00:48:42,378 --> 00:48:44,922
Crazy shit's been happening,
and I don't know why.

781
00:48:45,005 --> 00:48:46,966
Stop asking me. Okay?

782
00:48:47,466 --> 00:48:49,051
Wait. You're the paramedic.

783
00:48:50,803 --> 00:48:51,846
You saved my stepmother,

784
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:53,848
then you were
super awkward about it.

785
00:48:55,391 --> 00:48:58,519
That does sound like me.

786
00:48:58,602 --> 00:49:00,729
Wait. I recognize you too.

787
00:49:00,813 --> 00:49:02,022
What?

788
00:49:02,106 --> 00:49:04,191
Yeah. You live in my building.

789
00:49:04,984 --> 00:49:06,944
You leave your junk mail
in the lobby...

790
00:49:07,027 --> 00:49:08,988
and then everybody else
has to clean it up for you.

791
00:49:09,071 --> 00:49:11,615
Okay. Well, there should be
a recycling bin there.

792
00:49:12,032 --> 00:49:13,409
You don't think this is weird?

793
00:49:14,452 --> 00:49:15,661
That we both know you?

794
00:49:15,744 --> 00:49:16,745
It's honestly, like,

795
00:49:16,829 --> 00:49:18,956
the least weird thing
that's happened all day.

796
00:49:22,585 --> 00:49:23,586
What?

797
00:49:26,088 --> 00:49:27,089
Total stranger.

798
00:49:28,716 --> 00:49:29,717
No.

799
00:49:30,843 --> 00:49:31,969
You flipped me off.

800
00:49:32,720 --> 00:49:34,138
That's not really
narrowing it down much.

801
00:49:34,221 --> 00:49:35,931
You guys, this is so freaky.

802
00:49:36,265 --> 00:49:38,184
Who are you? What is going on?

803
00:49:40,644 --> 00:49:42,646
I can see the future.

804
00:49:44,106 --> 00:49:45,107
Kind of.

805
00:49:51,113 --> 00:49:52,114
I mean...

806
00:49:53,741 --> 00:49:54,783
What the hell?

807
00:49:54,867 --> 00:49:56,869
See? She didn't see that coming.

808
00:49:57,661 --> 00:49:58,954
It doesn't work like that.

809
00:49:59,038 --> 00:50:01,207
You guys,
just give her a chance, please.

810
00:50:01,290 --> 00:50:03,375
Wait. When you were looking
into the future...

811
00:50:03,459 --> 00:50:05,377
did you see us...

812
00:50:05,794 --> 00:50:07,922
in the middle of nowhere
eating glove-compartment jerky?

813
00:50:08,005 --> 00:50:11,091
Okay, look. Believe me or don't.
I don't care.

814
00:50:11,175 --> 00:50:13,677
I didn't ask
to be doing this with you.

815
00:50:14,053 --> 00:50:15,930
And I didn't ask for this
to happen to me, either.

816
00:50:16,388 --> 00:50:19,475
Also, I'm pretty sure
I saved all of your lives.

817
00:50:20,100 --> 00:50:22,228
So, you're welcome.

818
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:25,606
How does it work?

819
00:50:28,275 --> 00:50:29,527
It just happens.

820
00:50:29,610 --> 00:50:31,487
Can you do it now?

821
00:50:32,780 --> 00:50:34,198
I can't control it.

822
00:50:34,281 --> 00:50:37,243
You know the other guy can walk
on the ceiling, right?

823
00:50:37,326 --> 00:50:38,786
No, he can't.

824
00:50:40,412 --> 00:50:41,705
He was using his hands.

825
00:50:42,414 --> 00:50:43,624
Why are you like this?

826
00:50:43,707 --> 00:50:46,043
I'm just saying
it was more of a crawl.

827
00:50:46,126 --> 00:50:48,003
It was like a spider...

828
00:50:49,630 --> 00:50:50,631
person.

829
00:50:59,598 --> 00:51:02,434
I'm gonna be back
in a few hours.

830
00:51:04,103 --> 00:51:05,729
Where are you going?

831
00:51:05,813 --> 00:51:08,732
I need to check some things out
about all of this.

832
00:51:08,816 --> 00:51:11,527
You can't just leave us here.

833
00:51:11,610 --> 00:51:13,779
We'll be okay, Julia.
We don't need a babysitter.

834
00:51:13,862 --> 00:51:15,739
Yeah, sure. Just three teenagers
alone in the woods.

835
00:51:15,823 --> 00:51:17,908
Definitely not the opening
of a horror film.

836
00:51:17,992 --> 00:51:20,119
You are way safer out here.

837
00:51:20,619 --> 00:51:24,832
Just, you know,
be like a Girl Scout girl.

838
00:51:24,915 --> 00:51:26,875
Be that. Just be that.

839
00:51:26,959 --> 00:51:29,044
Can you bring us
some sandwiches?

840
00:51:29,128 --> 00:51:30,129
Cassie.

841
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:34,216
Can we trust you?

842
00:51:35,467 --> 00:51:37,595
Three hours. Okay?

843
00:51:37,678 --> 00:51:40,848
Just stay here.
And don't do anything dumb.

844
00:51:45,269 --> 00:51:48,480
Seriously. Don't do dumb things.

845
00:51:51,567 --> 00:51:53,110
She was talking to you.

846
00:51:53,193 --> 00:51:55,279
Okay, well,
you're just a bitch, so...

847
00:52:02,578 --> 00:52:03,704
I know tae Kwon do.

848
00:52:04,371 --> 00:52:05,372
You?

849
00:52:06,373 --> 00:52:08,542
Yeah, I had
a few rough years in school

850
00:52:08,626 --> 00:52:09,918
when my parents were divorcing.

851
00:52:10,002 --> 00:52:13,297
So I wanted to feel like I could
fight back if I needed to.

852
00:52:18,677 --> 00:52:19,928
That's what I thought.

853
00:53:33,377 --> 00:53:34,753
One second, cat.

854
00:53:38,090 --> 00:53:39,258
Come on.

855
00:53:43,303 --> 00:53:45,764
Research on Amazonian spiders...

856
00:53:46,974 --> 00:53:49,727
peptides, more peptides.

857
00:53:49,810 --> 00:53:51,186
Come on. Where is it?

858
00:53:53,772 --> 00:53:54,982
Spider people.

859
00:53:55,691 --> 00:53:57,192
<i>Las Arañas.</i>

860
00:53:58,861 --> 00:54:00,571
Have you ever heard
of <i>Las Arañas?</i>

861
00:54:02,281 --> 00:54:03,282
Me neither.

862
00:54:05,576 --> 00:54:08,162
"According to local folklore...

863
00:54:09,621 --> 00:54:13,000
"they possess powers
derived from spider venom...

864
00:54:14,293 --> 00:54:17,921
"and are incredibly fast,
incredibly strong...

865
00:54:19,548 --> 00:54:21,216
"and they can
climb like spiders."

866
00:54:23,552 --> 00:54:24,887
Just like ceiling guy.

867
00:54:31,351 --> 00:54:32,853
How would you know...

868
00:54:32,936 --> 00:54:36,815
if you could climb a wall
if you've never tried?

869
00:54:53,749 --> 00:54:56,168
Okay, let's not
mention that to anybody.

870
00:55:04,676 --> 00:55:08,305
<i>"Las Arañas</i> are said to possess
a sixth sense...

871
00:55:08,847 --> 00:55:11,517
"as if they had the ability
to glimpse the future."

872
00:55:25,405 --> 00:55:26,698
Oh, my God.

873
00:55:45,509 --> 00:55:46,844
Hey, who's got the jerky?

874
