01:04:34,954 --> 01:04:36,247
Oh, my God. Come on.

1025
01:04:40,168 --> 01:04:41,586
Seriously, dude.

1026
01:04:52,806 --> 01:04:53,890
Come on. Let's go.

1027
01:04:53,973 --> 01:04:55,809
Don't even pretend
that you're cooler than Britney.

1028
01:04:55,892 --> 01:04:56,935
I know you know the words.

1029
01:04:57,018 --> 01:04:58,812
Come on, get up here.

1030
01:04:59,396 --> 01:05:01,189
Hey!

1031
01:05:01,272 --> 01:05:02,524
You should totally
get up there, dog.

1032
01:05:03,316 --> 01:05:04,317
Come on.

1033
01:05:13,743 --> 01:05:15,412
Hey!

1034
01:05:19,541 --> 01:05:21,459
Guys. Guys, guys.
We have to go, we have to...

1035
01:05:30,218 --> 01:05:31,886
Girls, get in! Get in! Get in!

1036
01:05:31,970 --> 01:05:33,430
Leave everything. Run!

1037
01:05:34,222 --> 01:05:35,932
- Come on, let's go. Let's go!
- Mattie, come on!

1038
01:05:36,015 --> 01:05:37,642
- Get in!
- I'm so sorry, Cassie.

1039
01:05:56,286 --> 01:05:57,370
God!

1040
01:06:00,165 --> 01:06:01,958
So much
for not needing a babysitter.

1041
01:06:02,041 --> 01:06:04,294
Do you guys think of anybody
but yourselves?

1042
01:06:04,377 --> 01:06:06,421
You're so impulsive
and entitled,

1043
01:06:06,504 --> 01:06:07,505
and you don't listen!

1044
01:06:07,589 --> 01:06:08,882
- We didn't mean to...
- Whatever!

1045
01:06:08,965 --> 01:06:10,049
Don't even say anything!

1046
01:06:10,884 --> 01:06:11,885
God!

1047
01:06:12,469 --> 01:06:14,179
Your futures were almost...

1048
01:06:14,971 --> 01:06:16,097
so different.

1049
01:06:17,974 --> 01:06:19,684
You're lucky I saw them.

1050
01:06:19,767 --> 01:06:20,894
I'm so sorry.

1051
01:06:20,977 --> 01:06:21,978
Yes.

1052
01:06:22,896 --> 01:06:26,065
You should be so sorry.
All of you should be sorry.

1053
01:06:28,401 --> 01:06:29,402
God!

1054
01:06:52,842 --> 01:06:54,844
Amaria, where did they go?

1055
01:06:54,928 --> 01:06:56,721
<i>I'm running checks now.</i>

1056
01:06:57,931 --> 01:06:59,724
I don't understand
how they're doing this.

1057
01:06:59,807 --> 01:07:01,518
I've got a match on the woman
who's with them.

1058
01:07:01,893 --> 01:07:03,311
I'm not interested in her.

1059
01:07:03,811 --> 01:07:05,647
Focus on finding those girls.

1060
01:07:05,730 --> 01:07:06,981
Cassandra Webb.

1061
01:07:07,899 --> 01:07:09,901
Daughter of Constance Webb,
deceased.

1062
01:07:10,360 --> 01:07:11,653
Did you say, "Webb"?

1063
01:07:13,029 --> 01:07:14,447
Yeah. Do you know her?

1064
01:07:14,531 --> 01:07:15,949
That's not possible.

1065
01:07:18,535 --> 01:07:19,536
Come on.

1066
01:07:23,831 --> 01:07:26,292
He's not gonna stop
until he kills us, is he?

1067
01:07:27,460 --> 01:07:30,255
I don't know what he wants.
I don't know anything.

1068
01:07:32,131 --> 01:07:34,050
But you can see the future.

1069
01:07:34,968 --> 01:07:37,470
Can't you stop him
with your visions?

1070
01:07:37,554 --> 01:07:39,389
I don't know
how to control them.

1071
01:07:40,265 --> 01:07:41,474
It's useless.

1072
01:07:41,558 --> 01:07:43,351
Well, we're alive.
Maybe that's a plus.

1073
01:07:43,810 --> 01:07:44,811
Is your hand okay?

1074
01:07:46,563 --> 01:07:47,564
It's fine.

1075
01:07:52,694 --> 01:07:54,696
First thing in the morning,
I'm taking you all home.

1076
01:07:55,071 --> 01:07:56,489
Your parents can deal with this.

1077
01:07:57,865 --> 01:07:58,992
No, they can't.

1078
01:08:02,996 --> 01:08:04,289
My mom's in a psych ward.

1079
01:08:06,666 --> 01:08:08,418
She didn't really cope well
after my dad left...

1080
01:08:08,501 --> 01:08:11,212
and so, I got sent to live
with him and his new family...

1081
01:08:11,296 --> 01:08:13,006
and I don't think
that they want me there.

1082
01:08:16,509 --> 01:08:18,219
I wondered if they missed me...

1083
01:08:19,929 --> 01:08:21,139
if I ran away.

1084
01:08:22,890 --> 01:08:23,891
So you did.

1085
01:08:24,601 --> 01:08:25,935
My parents aren't around either.

1086
01:08:26,519 --> 01:08:29,230
I think they resent how having
a kid messed up their lives.

1087
01:08:29,814 --> 01:08:30,815
I don't think they're gonna

1088
01:08:30,898 --> 01:08:32,233
fly back from China
to deal with this.

1089
01:08:32,317 --> 01:08:34,319
And I really
don't wanna find out, so...

1090
01:08:35,028 --> 01:08:36,029
I'm on my own.

1091
01:08:38,906 --> 01:08:40,908
Well, fine.
Then you guys can just...

1092
01:08:42,243 --> 01:08:43,911
- go to the police.
- No.

1093
01:08:47,457 --> 01:08:50,126
My dad got deported
six months ago.

1094
01:08:51,252 --> 01:08:53,421
I came home from school,
and he was gone.

1095
01:08:53,838 --> 01:08:54,964
What about your mom?

1096
01:08:55,048 --> 01:08:56,841
My mom died when I was five.

1097
01:08:57,508 --> 01:08:58,509
It's just me and my dad.

1098
01:08:59,636 --> 01:09:01,387
Except he never told me
he didn't have his papers.

1099
01:09:01,471 --> 01:09:03,389
So, I've just been
living by myself

1100
01:09:03,473 --> 01:09:04,641
at our apartment since then.

1101
01:09:04,724 --> 01:09:05,725
You're on your own?

1102
01:09:07,060 --> 01:09:09,437
I don't need anyone else
to look out for me.

1103
01:09:11,564 --> 01:09:12,857
And I don't
have a curfew, either.

1104
01:09:16,277 --> 01:09:18,196
So, I can't go to the police.

1105
01:09:18,279 --> 01:09:19,280
Okay?

1106
01:09:19,781 --> 01:09:22,158
Until I'm 18, I can't exist.

1107
01:09:23,660 --> 01:09:25,787
And there's no way
I'm getting deported too.

1108
01:09:25,870 --> 01:09:28,206
Or going into the foster system.

1109
01:09:31,084 --> 01:09:32,085
Well...

1110
01:09:33,378 --> 01:09:35,963
Foster system
isn't always that terrible.

1111
01:09:39,384 --> 01:09:41,469
Things didn't turn out
so bad for me.

1112
01:09:42,011 --> 01:09:43,012
Right.

1113
01:09:46,391 --> 01:09:47,809
Cassie, please help us.

1114
01:12:09,325 --> 01:12:12,578
No one survives once enough
poison enters their system.

1115
01:12:12,662 --> 01:12:14,539
You won't be so lucky next time.

1116
01:12:15,248 --> 01:12:16,874
Why are you doing this?

1117
01:12:17,750 --> 01:12:19,669
I need to stop them
from killing me.

1118
01:12:20,711 --> 01:12:23,297
They're not killers.
They're just teenagers.

1119
01:12:23,714 --> 01:12:25,550
In the future,
they become much more.

1120
01:12:25,633 --> 01:12:29,846
In the future, they will destroy
me and everything I've built.

1121
01:12:31,514 --> 01:12:33,057
Those girls cannot exist.

1122
01:12:34,016 --> 01:12:35,560
How come you get to decide?

1123
01:12:36,143 --> 01:12:38,020
Because I'm the one
with the powers.

1124
01:12:41,858 --> 01:12:45,444
If you knew what I knew,
you'd do the same thing.

1125
01:12:47,321 --> 01:12:48,489
Would I?

1126
01:12:48,573 --> 01:12:51,784
If I knew the price to pay
was the lives of three girls?

1127
01:12:51,868 --> 01:12:53,536
The only thing I know is that,

1128
01:12:53,619 --> 01:12:55,830
in the future,
they also have powers.

1129
01:12:57,874 --> 01:13:01,210
The girls? The girls have powers
in the future?

1130
01:13:01,294 --> 01:13:03,546
Did you think you could beat me
with your mind?

1131
01:13:04,589 --> 01:13:06,465
Your mother underestimated me.

1132
01:13:08,384 --> 01:13:09,677
The power of the spider.

1133
01:13:10,636 --> 01:13:12,555
Don't make the same mistake.

1134
01:13:13,055 --> 01:13:14,140
Tell me where they are!

1135
01:13:14,849 --> 01:13:16,058
They don't mean anything to you.

1136
01:13:17,727 --> 01:13:19,145
You could just walk away.

1137
01:14:14,909 --> 01:14:16,619
What is this?

1138
01:14:20,998 --> 01:14:22,208
Rise and shine.

1139
01:14:23,042 --> 01:14:25,252
Okay, so this guy's hands

1140
01:14:25,336 --> 01:14:27,922
somehow release
an acute neurotoxin...

1141
01:14:28,005 --> 01:14:30,549
and it is painful. I was lucky.

1142
01:14:30,633 --> 01:14:32,176
The longer he holds on to you,

1143
01:14:32,259 --> 01:14:34,345
the more poison
gets into your system.

1144
01:14:34,428 --> 01:14:35,429
Then what happens?

1145
01:14:36,847 --> 01:14:38,182
Then your heart stops.

1146
01:14:39,767 --> 01:14:42,812
But you can offset
cardiac arrest with CPR.

1147
01:14:43,437 --> 01:14:46,524
So you interlock your hands
like this.

1148
01:14:47,274 --> 01:14:48,567
You lock your elbows...

1149
01:14:48,985 --> 01:14:51,237
and then you place
the heel of your hand

1150
01:14:51,320 --> 01:14:53,572
right on the sternum. Okay?

1151
01:14:53,656 --> 01:14:54,657
And then you pump.

1152
01:14:54,740 --> 01:14:56,993
And you wanna go,
like, two inches down.

1153
01:14:57,368 --> 01:15:00,204
And you wanna keep
a rhythm like a heartbeat. Okay?

1154
01:15:00,830 --> 01:15:01,914
You ready?

1155
01:15:01,998 --> 01:15:04,125
Okay, begin compressions.
Go. Good.

1156
01:15:06,168 --> 01:15:07,503
Okay. And when do I stop?

1157
01:15:07,586 --> 01:15:09,338
You don't stop.
If you stop, they die.

1158
01:15:10,631 --> 01:15:11,632
And if you get tired,

1159
01:15:11,716 --> 01:15:13,342
then you need
somebody to take over.

1160
01:15:14,176 --> 01:15:15,428
- I'm getting kinda tired.
- Okay.

1161
01:15:15,511 --> 01:15:17,596
- Anya, get ready to take over.
- Mm-hmm.

1162
01:15:17,680 --> 01:15:20,558
But you have to pick up
the exact same rhythm.

1163
01:15:20,641 --> 01:15:21,642
- Yeah.
- Ready?

1164
01:15:21,726 --> 01:15:22,977
- Yep.
- And go.

1165
01:15:26,313 --> 01:15:28,399
Great. Nice, Mattie.

1166
01:15:28,482 --> 01:15:29,483
Not cool.

1167
01:15:32,236 --> 01:15:34,071
Julia, you wanna take over?
Okay.

1168
01:15:35,281 --> 01:15:36,282
Get ready.

1169
01:15:38,409 --> 01:15:41,537
Okay. One, two, three. Perfect.

1170
01:15:41,620 --> 01:15:42,913
Nice job, Anya.

1171
01:15:45,416 --> 01:15:47,626
I've never said this before
in my entire life...

1172
01:15:48,544 --> 01:15:49,712
but you're a good teacher.

1173
01:15:52,006 --> 01:15:55,843
Well, I've been
learning some things too.

1174
01:15:58,054 --> 01:15:59,346
About my mom.

1175
01:16:06,145 --> 01:16:07,438
Wait, so you do know this guy.

1176
01:16:08,147 --> 01:16:09,648
My mom did. I think.

1177
01:16:09,732 --> 01:16:10,983
That's her.

1178
01:16:11,067 --> 01:16:12,359
She's really pretty.

1179
01:16:16,655 --> 01:16:18,491
So this is because of you?

1180
01:16:20,868 --> 01:16:23,788
All I know is that
she was researching spiders.

1181
01:16:24,747 --> 01:16:26,624
In her notebook,
there's some stuff...

1182
01:16:26,707 --> 01:16:31,462
about a local tribe in Peru
that can do, like, crazy stuff.

1183
01:16:31,545 --> 01:16:33,255
What kind of crazy stuff?

1184
01:16:34,757 --> 01:16:36,634
Climb like spiders.

1185
01:16:38,260 --> 01:16:40,971
So is he one of them?

1186
01:16:41,764 --> 01:16:43,390
I need more information.

1187
01:16:47,186 --> 01:16:48,187
You're leaving.

1188
01:16:52,191 --> 01:16:54,401
I have to go and figure out
what is going on.

1189
01:16:54,902 --> 01:16:55,903
How?

1190
01:16:58,906 --> 01:17:00,282
You have to go to Peru.

1191
01:17:03,744 --> 01:17:04,745
I'll be gone a week.

1192
01:17:04,829 --> 01:17:05,830
I don't wanna leave them,

1193
01:17:05,913 --> 01:17:07,248
but he's out there
looking for them...

1194
01:17:07,331 --> 01:17:08,332
and they're relying on me,

1195
01:17:08,415 --> 01:17:09,708
and I don't know how else
to protect them.

1196
01:17:09,792 --> 01:17:12,086
Okay, look, I'm staying
with Mary for a few weeks

1197
01:17:12,169 --> 01:17:13,295
while Richard's out of town.

1198
01:17:13,379 --> 01:17:15,506
He won't find them there.
But, Cassie...

1199
01:17:16,715 --> 01:17:19,426
I can't pretend to understand
what's going on here.

1200
01:17:19,510 --> 01:17:21,887
Just be careful, okay?

1201
01:17:21,971 --> 01:17:23,222
I'll be back as soon as I can.

1202
01:17:23,305 --> 01:17:25,307
Thank you, Ben.
You didn't ask for any of this.

1203
01:17:25,391 --> 01:17:27,226
Okay, well, neither did you.

1204
01:19:54,039 --> 01:19:56,834
You have come back
looking for answers.

1205
01:20:00,879 --> 01:20:01,880
Back?

1206
01:20:01,964 --> 01:20:04,049
I promised your mother
I would be here.

1207
01:20:07,511 --> 01:20:10,014
My mom thought
<i>Las Arañas</i> were a myth.

1208
01:20:10,097 --> 01:20:11,307
What do you think?

1209
01:20:11,390 --> 01:20:14,018
I think she was crazy
for coming here alone.

1210
01:20:14,101 --> 01:20:15,519
She came here

1211
01:20:15,602 --> 01:20:18,397
hoping to extract healing
properties from the spiders.

1212
01:20:18,480 --> 01:20:20,524
She thought
she was being protected.

1213
01:20:20,607 --> 01:20:21,817
By Ezekiel Sims?

1214
01:20:21,900 --> 01:20:23,819
His motives were selfish.

1215
01:20:23,902 --> 01:20:25,696
He used your mom to find us.

1216
01:20:25,779 --> 01:20:27,406
But, because
he stole the spider...

1217
01:20:27,489 --> 01:20:28,615
he was cursed.

1218
01:20:29,408 --> 01:20:32,328
And he's been trying to outrun
his destiny ever since.

1219
01:20:39,209 --> 01:20:40,836
This is where my mom died?

1220
01:20:41,712 --> 01:20:43,339
And where you were born.

1221
01:20:48,802 --> 01:20:52,097
I don't understand why
she risked my life to come here.

1222
01:20:53,015 --> 01:20:55,225
To see the future clearly...

1223
01:20:55,309 --> 01:20:57,519
you have
to heal the wounds of your past.

1224
01:20:57,603 --> 01:20:58,645
That sounds like literally

1225
01:20:58,729 --> 01:21:01,065
every therapy session
I've ever avoided.

1226
01:21:01,148 --> 01:21:03,609
You have to go
back to your beginning

1227
01:21:03,692 --> 01:21:04,985
and keep going past that.

1228
01:21:05,069 --> 01:21:06,111
There are powers

1229
01:21:06,195 --> 01:21:08,364
you don't even know
you're capable of.

1230
01:21:09,531 --> 01:21:12,659
Your thread did not start
when you were born.

1231
01:21:16,372 --> 01:21:17,539
Do you trust me?

1232
01:21:19,958 --> 01:21:21,919
Not really sure at this point
I have a choice.

1233
01:21:30,469 --> 01:21:31,804
<i>You could just walk away.</i>

1234
01:21:31,887 --> 01:21:34,390
<i>Your thread did not start
when you were born.</i>

1235
01:21:35,599 --> 01:21:37,559
<i>They're almost
impossible to find.</i>

1236
01:21:38,394 --> 01:21:40,896
She really is trying her best
to keep me from working.

1237
01:21:40,979 --> 01:21:42,189
<i>Not when I'm this close.</i>

1238
01:21:42,272 --> 01:21:43,690
But I'm not
gonna let her do that.

1239
01:21:43,774 --> 01:21:45,859
Why did you hate me so much?

1240
01:21:45,943 --> 01:21:46,944
Thank you.

1241
01:21:47,027 --> 01:21:48,278
<i>For the umbrella.</i>

1242
01:21:49,405 --> 01:21:50,697
<i>-Give it to me.
- No.</i>

1243
01:21:51,281 --> 01:21:52,449
I found it.

1244
01:21:52,533 --> 01:21:53,534
I found the spider.

1245
01:21:54,410 --> 01:21:55,828
Incredible, isn't it?

1246
01:21:57,913 --> 01:21:59,832
- Give it to me.
- No, please.

1247
01:21:59,915 --> 01:22:00,916
Give it to me.

1248
01:22:00,999 --> 01:22:02,000
<i>You're making
the wrong decision.</i>

1249
01:22:02,084 --> 01:22:03,752
- You could just walk away.
<i>-No, you're making the wrong...</i>

1250
01:22:16,640 --> 01:22:19,017
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm...

1251
01:22:19,810 --> 01:22:22,479
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

1252
01:22:24,481 --> 01:22:26,442
Las Arañas <i>could not stand by.</i>

1253
01:22:27,151 --> 01:22:29,153
<i>We tried to save you both.</i>

1254
01:22:47,045 --> 01:22:49,006
Her journey will not be easy...

1255
01:22:49,840 --> 01:22:51,550
but she is strong.

1256
01:23:00,559 --> 01:23:02,769
Your test results came back.

1257
01:23:02,853 --> 01:23:03,937
I'm sorry to tell you

1258
01:23:04,021 --> 01:23:06,607
that your baby has
myasthenia gravis.

1259
01:23:06,690 --> 01:23:09,693
It's a genetic
neuromuscular disorder.

1260
01:23:09,776 --> 01:23:11,487
<i>But I don't have
a neuromuscular disorder.</i>

1261
01:23:11,570 --> 01:23:14,281
Life expectancy varies.

1262
01:23:14,364 --> 01:23:16,116
Do you need a tissue?

1263
01:23:16,200 --> 01:23:17,910
No. No. I need a cure.

1264
01:23:17,993 --> 01:23:20,496
I'm afraid there is no cure.

1265
01:23:20,913 --> 01:23:23,165
Single target
nucleotide intervention.

1266
01:23:23,665 --> 01:23:25,083
<i>It's experimental...</i>

1267
01:23:25,375 --> 01:23:27,586
but there are some promising
leads in the Amazon.

1268
01:23:27,669 --> 01:23:29,296
That's why you went there?

1269
01:23:29,796 --> 01:23:30,797
For me?

1270
01:23:30,881 --> 01:23:33,300
I have to advise you against
traveling in your condition.

1271
01:23:33,383 --> 01:23:36,386
I'm sorry, what are you offering
besides tissues?

1272
01:23:36,470 --> 01:23:38,305
I know this is hard to accept.

1273
01:23:38,388 --> 01:23:39,890
No, no, I am...

1274
01:23:39,973 --> 01:23:43,977
I'm unwilling to accept
a diagnosis of helplessness.

1275
01:23:45,103 --> 01:23:47,314
And I'm not gonna
teach my daughter to either.

1276
01:23:56,949 --> 01:23:57,950
You did it.

1277
01:23:59,826 --> 01:24:00,911
You did it.

